    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '2. The following is NOT classified as a cardiomyopathy in the strict sense of the word: a.dilated cardiomyopathy b.arrhythmogenic right ventricular dysplasia c.hypertrophic cardiomyopathy d.severe aortic stenosis e.restrictive cardiomyopathy',
    'text_answer': 'severe aortic stenosis',
    'topic_text': '2. The following is NOT classified as a cardiomyopathy in the strict sense of the word: a.dilated cardiomyopathy b.arrhythmogenic right ventricular dysplasia c.hypertrophic cardiomyopathy d.severe aortic stenosis e.restrictive cardiomyopathy',
    'context': 'Table 2.69 – Classification of Cardiomyopathies According to World Health Organization Criteria Functional Classification of Cardiomyopathies Dilated cardiomyopathy Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy Restrictive cardiomyopathy Arrhythmogenic cardiomyopathy Unclassified cardiomyopathies Specific Cardiomyopathies Ischemic cardiomyopathy Valvular cardiomyopathy Hypertensive cardiomyopathy Inflammatory Cardiomyopathy: Idiopathic Autoimmune Infectious Metabolic Cardiomyopathy: Endocrine Congenital metabolic disorders Amyloidosis Cardiomyopathy in Systemic Diseases: Connective tissue diseases Infiltrative diseases and granulomatoses Muscular dystrophies Neuromuscular diseases Hypersensitivity and toxic reactions Peripartum cardiomyopathy',
    'text': 'Context: Table 2.69 – Classification of Cardiomyopathies According to World Health Organization Criteria Functional Classification of Cardiomyopathies Dilated cardiomyopathy Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy Restrictive cardiomyopathy Arrhythmogenic cardiomyopathy Unclassified cardiomyopathies Specific Cardiomyopathies Ischemic cardiomyopathy Valvular cardiomyopathy Hypertensive cardiomyopathy Inflammatory Cardiomyopathy: Idiopathic Autoimmune Infectious Metabolic Cardiomyopathy: Endocrine Congenital metabolic disorders Amyloidosis Cardiomyopathy in Systemic Diseases: Connective tissue diseases Infiltrative diseases and granulomatoses Muscular dystrophies Neuromuscular diseases Hypersensitivity and toxic reactions Peripartum cardiomyopathy Supporting answer: severe aortic stenosis'
  },
{
    'id': 3,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '3. What is true about the third heart sound? A. It is always a pathological finding B. It is a low-frequency sound C. We hear it just before the first heart sound D. The loudness is not proportional to its clinical significance E. It is rarely heard in heart failure',
    'text_answer': 'It is a low-frequency sound',
    'topic_text': '3. What is true about the third heart sound? A. It is always a pathological finding B. It is a low-frequency sound C. We hear it just before the first heart sound D. The loudness is not proportional to its clinical significance E. It is rarely heard in heart failure',
    'context': 'Tretji ton nastane zaradi vibracij prekatnih sten ob nenadni omejitvi raztezanja v času najhitrejše polnitve prekatov v zgodnji diastoli. Je bolj nizkofrekvenčen in običajno tišji od prvega in drugega tona. Skupaj s prvim in drugim tonom spominja na galop in ga opisujemo kot protodiastolični ali ventrikularni galop. English: The third heart sound arises due to vibrations of the ventricular walls when there is a sudden limitation of expansion during the most rapid filling phase of the ventricles in early diastole. It is lower in frequency and usually quieter than the first and second heart sounds. Together with the first and second sounds, it resembles a gallop and is described as a protodiastolic or ventricular gallop.',
    'text': 'Context: Tretji ton nastane zaradi vibracij prekatnih sten ob nenadni omejitvi raztezanja v času najhitrejše polnitve prekatov v zgodnji diastoli. Je bolj nizkofrekvenčen in običajno tišji od prvega in drugega tona. Skupaj s prvim in drugim tonom spominja na galop in ga opisujemo kot protodiastolični ali ventrikularni galop. English: The third heart sound arises due to vibrations of the ventricular walls when there is a sudden limitation of expansion during the most rapid filling phase of the ventricles in early diastole. It is lower in frequency and usually quieter than the first and second heart sounds. Together with the first and second sounds, it resembles a gallop and is described as a protodiastolic or ventricular gallop. Supporting answer: It is a low-frequency sound'
  },
{
    'id': 4,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '4. What does hemoptysis mean? A. Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 ml in 24 hours B. Vomiting blood C. Coughing up blood-streaked sputum D. Passing bloody stool E. Bloody expectoration',
    'text_answer': 'Coughing up blood-streaked sputum',
    'topic_text': '4. What does hemoptysis mean? A. Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 ml in 24 hours B. Vomiting blood C. Coughing up blood-streaked sputum D. Passing bloody stool E. Bloody expectoration',
    'context': 'Opredelitev. Izkašeljaj s primesjo manjše ali večje količine sveže ali že delno hematinizirane krvi imenujemo hemoptiza. Če je kri edina sestavina izmečka in jo bolnik izkašlja več kot 250 ml/24 ur, govorimo o hemoptoi. Po navadi krvavitev izvira iz bronhialne cirkulacije. English: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a small or large amount of fresh or partially hemolyzed blood is called hemoptysis. If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up more than 250 ml in 24 hours, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe). The bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. English: Definition.A vacation with a substance of smaller or larger amounts of fresh or partially hematinized blood is called hemoptysis.If the blood is the only ingredient in the scum and the patient coughs it for more than 250 ml/24 hours, we are talking about hemoptoi.Usually bleeding originates from bronchial circulation.ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a Small or Large amount of Fresh or partially hemolyzed Blood is called hemoptysis.If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up the more than 250 ml and 24 house, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe).The Bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation.',
    'text': 'Context: Opredelitev. Izkašeljaj s primesjo manjše ali večje količine sveže ali že delno hematinizirane krvi imenujemo hemoptiza. Če je kri edina sestavina izmečka in jo bolnik izkašlja več kot 250 ml/24 ur, govorimo o hemoptoi. Po navadi krvavitev izvira iz bronhialne cirkulacije. English: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a small or large amount of fresh or partially hemolyzed blood is called hemoptysis. If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up more than 250 ml in 24 hours, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe). The bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. English: Definition.A vacation with a substance of smaller or larger amounts of fresh or partially hematinized blood is called hemoptysis.If the blood is the only ingredient in the scum and the patient coughs it for more than 250 ml/24 hours, we are talking about hemoptoi.Usually bleeding originates from bronchial circulation.ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a Small or Large amount of Fresh or partially hemolyzed Blood is called hemoptysis.If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up the more than 250 ml and 24 house, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe).The Bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. Supporting answer: Coughing up blood-streaked sputum'
  },
{
    'id': 5,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '5. How is orthostatic hypotension defined? a. If a drop in systolic blood pressure is detected when the patient stands up from a supine position b. If a drop in both systolic and diastolic blood pressure is detected when the patient stands up from a supine position c. If the patient experiences syncope or dizziness when standing up from a supine position d. If blood pressure falls by at least 30/20 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position e. If blood pressure falls by at least 60/30 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position',
    'text_answer': 'If blood pressure falls by at least 30/20 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position',
    'topic_text': '5. How is orthostatic hypotension defined? a. If a drop in systolic blood pressure is detected when the patient stands up from a supine position b. If a drop in both systolic and diastolic blood pressure is detected when the patient stands up from a supine position c. If the patient experiences syncope or dizziness when standing up from a supine position d. If blood pressure falls by at least 30/20 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position e. If blood pressure falls by at least 60/30 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position',
    'context': 'O ortostatski hipotenziji govorimo, če je tlak stoje vsaj za 30/20 mmHg nižji v primerjavi z meritvijo v leže. Ugotavljanje takšne razlike tlaka med ležečim in stoječim položajem je posebej pomembno pri bolnikih s sumom na feokromocitom (ki imajo zmanjšan volumen plazme in oslabljenje reflekse simpatičnega živčevja), pri sladkornih bolnikih (prizadetost žilnih živcev) in vseh, ki jemljejo zdravila za zniževanje tlaka. English: we speak of orthostatic hypotension if the blood pressure when standing is at least 30/20 mmHg lower compared to the measurement in the supine position. Assessing such a difference in pressure between the supine and standing positions is particularly important in patients suspected of pheochromocytoma (who have reduced plasma volume and impaired sympathetic nervous system reflexes), in diabetic patients (vascular neuropathy), and in anyone taking blood pressure–lowering medications.',
    'text': 'Context: O ortostatski hipotenziji govorimo, če je tlak stoje vsaj za 30/20 mmHg nižji v primerjavi z meritvijo v leže. Ugotavljanje takšne razlike tlaka med ležečim in stoječim položajem je posebej pomembno pri bolnikih s sumom na feokromocitom (ki imajo zmanjšan volumen plazme in oslabljenje reflekse simpatičnega živčevja), pri sladkornih bolnikih (prizadetost žilnih živcev) in vseh, ki jemljejo zdravila za zniževanje tlaka. English: we speak of orthostatic hypotension if the blood pressure when standing is at least 30/20 mmHg lower compared to the measurement in the supine position. Assessing such a difference in pressure between the supine and standing positions is particularly important in patients suspected of pheochromocytoma (who have reduced plasma volume and impaired sympathetic nervous system reflexes), in diabetic patients (vascular neuropathy), and in anyone taking blood pressure–lowering medications. Supporting answer: If blood pressure falls by at least 30/20 mm Hg when the patient stands up from a supine position'
  },
{
    'id': 6,
