    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '8. “Organic murmur” means: a. Pathologically altered hemodynamics b. The cause is in another organ c. The heart is morphologically changed d. The cause is in artificial material e. It is not a sign of heart disease',
    'text_answer': 'The heart is morphologically changed',
    'topic_text': '8. “Organic murmur” means: a. Pathologically altered hemodynamics b. The cause is in another organ c. The heart is morphologically changed d. The cause is in artificial material e. It is not a sign of heart disease',
    'context': 'Vzroki so lahko morfološke spremembe (t. i. organski šumi) ali bolezensko spremenjena hemodinamika (t. i. funkcionalni šumi). Šume najdemo včasih tudi pri zdravih ljudeh – predvsem pri otrocih, lahko tudi pri starostnikih (t. i. akcidetalni ali naključni šumi). English: The causes can be morphological changes (so-called organic murmurs) or pathologically altered hemodynamics (so-called functional murmurs). Murmurs are sometimes heard even in healthy individuals—especially in children, and also in the elderly (so-called accidental or incidental murmurs).',
    'text': 'Context: Vzroki so lahko morfološke spremembe (t. i. organski šumi) ali bolezensko spremenjena hemodinamika (t. i. funkcionalni šumi). Šume najdemo včasih tudi pri zdravih ljudeh – predvsem pri otrocih, lahko tudi pri starostnikih (t. i. akcidetalni ali naključni šumi). English: The causes can be morphological changes (so-called organic murmurs) or pathologically altered hemodynamics (so-called functional murmurs). Murmurs are sometimes heard even in healthy individuals—especially in children, and also in the elderly (so-called accidental or incidental murmurs). Supporting answer: The heart is morphologically changed'
  },
