    'question': '9. An accidental (incidental) murmur is: a. A consequence of trauma (e.g., a motor vehicle accident with blunt chest injury) b. Randomly detected in the early phase of heart disease c. Most common in children d. Soft and most often diastolic e. Most often a consequence of aortic stenosis',
    'text_answer': 'Most common in children',
    'topic_text': '9. An accidental (incidental) murmur is: a. A consequence of trauma (e.g., a motor vehicle accident with blunt chest injury) b. Randomly detected in the early phase of heart disease c. Most common in children d. Soft and most often diastolic e. Most often a consequence of aortic stenosis',
    'context': 'Vzroki so lahko morfološke spremembe (t. i. organski šumi) ali bolezensko spremenjena hemodinamika (t. i. funkcionalni šumi). Šume najdemo včasih tudi pri zdravih ljudeh – predvsem pri otrocih, lahko tudi pri starostnikih (t. i. akcidetalni ali naključni šumi). English: The causes can be morphological changes (so-called organic murmurs) or pathologically altered hemodynamics (so-called functional murmurs). Murmurs are sometimes heard even in healthy individuals—especially in children, and also in the elderly (so-called accidental or incidental murmurs).',
    'text': 'Context: Vzroki so lahko morfološke spremembe (t. i. organski šumi) ali bolezensko spremenjena hemodinamika (t. i. funkcionalni šumi). Šume najdemo včasih tudi pri zdravih ljudeh – predvsem pri otrocih, lahko tudi pri starostnikih (t. i. akcidetalni ali naključni šumi). English: The causes can be morphological changes (so-called organic murmurs) or pathologically altered hemodynamics (so-called functional murmurs). Murmurs are sometimes heard even in healthy individuals—especially in children, and also in the elderly (so-called accidental or incidental murmurs). Supporting answer: Most common in children'
  },
{
    'id': 10,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '10. Pulmonary embolism most often arises from a clot originating from: a. The large veins of the legs b. The large veins of the arms c. The calf (tibial) veins d. The pelvic veins e. The clot forms in the lungs',
    'text_answer': 'The large veins of the legs',
    'topic_text': '10. Pulmonary embolism most often arises from a clot originating from: a. The large veins of the legs b. The large veins of the arms c. The calf (tibial) veins d. The pelvic veins e. The clot forms in the lungs',
    'context': 'Opredelitev. Pljučna embolija je zamašitev ene ali več pljučnih arterij. To poglavje obravnava pljučne embolije, ki nastanejo zaradi krvnih strdkov. Ti nastanejo večinoma v venah nog, redkeje rok, ali v medeničnih venah. Krvni tok jih potem odnese v pljučne arterije. Definition. Pulmonary embolism is the occlusion of one or more pulmonary arteries. This section covers pulmonary embolisms that arise from blood clots. These clots most often form in the veins of the legs, less commonly in the arm veins, or in the pelvic veins. The bloodstream then carries them into the pulmonary arteries. English: Definition.pulmonary embolism is a clogging of one or more pulmonary arteries.This chapter deals with pulmonary embolism resulting from blood clots.These occur mostly in the veins of the legs, less often, or in the pelvic veins.The blood flow then takes them to the pulmonary arteries. Definition.pulmonary embolism is the occlusion of one or more pulmonary arteries.This section covers pulmonary embolisms that arise from blood clots.These Clots Most Optten Form in the Veins of the Legs, Less Commonly in the Arm Veins, Or in the Pelvic Veins.The Bloodstream then Carries Them Into the Pulmonary Arteries.',
    'text': 'Context: Opredelitev. Pljučna embolija je zamašitev ene ali več pljučnih arterij. To poglavje obravnava pljučne embolije, ki nastanejo zaradi krvnih strdkov. Ti nastanejo večinoma v venah nog, redkeje rok, ali v medeničnih venah. Krvni tok jih potem odnese v pljučne arterije. Definition. Pulmonary embolism is the occlusion of one or more pulmonary arteries. This section covers pulmonary embolisms that arise from blood clots. These clots most often form in the veins of the legs, less commonly in the arm veins, or in the pelvic veins. The bloodstream then carries them into the pulmonary arteries. English: Definition.pulmonary embolism is a clogging of one or more pulmonary arteries.This chapter deals with pulmonary embolism resulting from blood clots.These occur mostly in the veins of the legs, less often, or in the pelvic veins.The blood flow then takes them to the pulmonary arteries. Definition.pulmonary embolism is the occlusion of one or more pulmonary arteries.This section covers pulmonary embolisms that arise from blood clots.These Clots Most Optten Form in the Veins of the Legs, Less Commonly in the Arm Veins, Or in the Pelvic Veins.The Bloodstream then Carries Them Into the Pulmonary Arteries. Supporting answer: The large veins of the legs'
  },
{
    'id': 11,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '11. A patient suddenly loses consciousness and falls to the ground. After a few seconds, consciousness returns. Such an event is called: a. Psychogenic coma b. Opisthotonus c. Decortication d. Syncope e. Asystole',
    'text_answer': 'Syncope',
    'topic_text': '11. A patient suddenly loses consciousness and falls to the ground. After a few seconds, consciousness returns. Such an event is called: a. Psychogenic coma b. Opisthotonus c. Decortication d. Syncope e. Asystole',
    'context': 'Sinkopa je kratkotrajna izguba zavesti zaradi akutno zmanjšanega pretoka krvi v možganih. Nastane lahko nenadoma ali po prodromalnih simptomih (omotica, vrtoglavica, motnje vida, oblijevanje vročine, potenje, navzea). English: Syncope is a brief loss of consciousness due to an acute reduction of blood flow to the brain. It can occur suddenly or following prodromal symptoms (lightheadedness, dizziness, visual disturbances, a feeling of warmth, sweating, nausea).',
    'text': 'Context: Sinkopa je kratkotrajna izguba zavesti zaradi akutno zmanjšanega pretoka krvi v možganih. Nastane lahko nenadoma ali po prodromalnih simptomih (omotica, vrtoglavica, motnje vida, oblijevanje vročine, potenje, navzea). English: Syncope is a brief loss of consciousness due to an acute reduction of blood flow to the brain. It can occur suddenly or following prodromal symptoms (lightheadedness, dizziness, visual disturbances, a feeling of warmth, sweating, nausea). Supporting answer: Syncope'
  },
{
    'id': 12,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '12. Which of the following is characteristic of hypertrophic cardiomyopathy? a. The walls of the heart muscle are of normal thickness b. The disease is inherited in an autosomal dominant manner c. All four cardiac chambers are enlarged d. The only possible treatment is heart transplantation e. Patients never experience rhythm disturbances',
    'text_answer': 'The disease is inherited in an autosomal dominant manner',
    'topic_text': '12. Which of the following is characteristic of hypertrophic cardiomyopathy? a. The walls of the heart muscle are of normal thickness b. The disease is inherited in an autosomal dominant manner c. All four cardiac chambers are enlarged d. The only possible treatment is heart transplantation e. Patients never experience rhythm disturbances',
    'context': 'Etiopatogeneza. Hipertrofična kardiomiopatija se v 60 odstotkih deduje večinoma avtosomno dominantno. Gre za mutacije v genih za sarkomerne proteine. V 5–10 odstotkih gre za genetske motnje, ki vključujejo metabolične in nevromuskularne bolezni, kromosomske nepravilnosti in genetske sindrome. English: Etiopathogenesis. In about 60 percent of cases, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy is inherited, most often in an autosomal dominant pattern. It is caused by mutations in genes encoding sarcomeric proteins. In 5–10 percent of cases it is due to genetic disorders that include metabolic and neuromuscular diseases, chromosomal abnormalities, and genetic syndromes.',
    'text': 'Context: Etiopatogeneza. Hipertrofična kardiomiopatija se v 60 odstotkih deduje večinoma avtosomno dominantno. Gre za mutacije v genih za sarkomerne proteine. V 5–10 odstotkih gre za genetske motnje, ki vključujejo metabolične in nevromuskularne bolezni, kromosomske nepravilnosti in genetske sindrome. English: Etiopathogenesis. In about 60 percent of cases, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy is inherited, most often in an autosomal dominant pattern. It is caused by mutations in genes encoding sarcomeric proteins. In 5–10 percent of cases it is due to genetic disorders that include metabolic and neuromuscular diseases, chromosomal abnormalities, and genetic syndromes. Supporting answer: The disease is inherited in an autosomal dominant manner'
  },
{
    'id': 13,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Multi-vector RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '13. What is cardiac index? a. Heart rate divided by body surface area b. Heart rate divided by body-mass index c. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body surface area d. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body mass × 100 e. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body-mass index',
    'text_answer': 'Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body surface area',
    'topic_text': '13. What is cardiac index? a. Heart rate divided by body surface area b. Heart rate divided by body-mass index c. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body surface area d. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body mass × 100 e. Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body-mass index',
    'context': 'Zaradi razlik v telesni masi in višini so vrednosti minutnega volumna srca med posamezniki težko primerljive, zato jih delimo s telesno površino; ta količnik imenujemo srčni indeks: CI = MV / telesna površina Pri tem pomeni MV minutni volumen srca [l/min], CI pa srčni indeks [l/min/m²]. Normalne vrednosti srčnega indeksa v mirovanju znašajo od 2,6 do 4,2 l/min/m². S pomočjo Fickove ali termodilucijske metode dobimo tudi podatke, potrebne za izračun pljučnega in sistemskega žilnega upora, ki sta pogosto pomembna za odločitev o operaciji ali presaditvi srca. English: Because differences in body mass and height make resting cardiac output values difficult to compare between individuals, we divide by body surface area; this ratio is called the cardiac index: CI = CO / body surface area Here, CO denotes cardiac output [L/min], and CI the cardiac index [L/min/m²]. Normal resting values for the cardiac index range from 2.6 to 4.2 L/min/m². Using the Fick or thermodilution method, we also obtain data needed to calculate pulmonary and systemic vascular resistance, which is often important in decisions about heart surgery or transplantation.',
    'text': 'Context: Zaradi razlik v telesni masi in višini so vrednosti minutnega volumna srca med posamezniki težko primerljive, zato jih delimo s telesno površino; ta količnik imenujemo srčni indeks: CI = MV / telesna površina Pri tem pomeni MV minutni volumen srca [l/min], CI pa srčni indeks [l/min/m²]. Normalne vrednosti srčnega indeksa v mirovanju znašajo od 2,6 do 4,2 l/min/m². S pomočjo Fickove ali termodilucijske metode dobimo tudi podatke, potrebne za izračun pljučnega in sistemskega žilnega upora, ki sta pogosto pomembna za odločitev o operaciji ali presaditvi srca. English: Because differences in body mass and height make resting cardiac output values difficult to compare between individuals, we divide by body surface area; this ratio is called the cardiac index: CI = CO / body surface area Here, CO denotes cardiac output [L/min], and CI the cardiac index [L/min/m²]. Normal resting values for the cardiac index range from 2.6 to 4.2 L/min/m². Using the Fick or thermodilution method, we also obtain data needed to calculate pulmonary and systemic vascular resistance, which is often important in decisions about heart surgery or transplantation. Supporting answer: Cardiac output (minute volume) divided by body surface area'
  },
{
    'id': 14,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'review',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '14. In atrial flutter, the atrial rate limit is: a. Below 220/min b. Above 350/min c. 220–350/min d. 120–250/min e. 280–390/min',
    'text_answer': '220–350/min',
    'topic_text': '14. In atrial flutter, the atrial rate limit is: a. Below 220/min b. Above 350/min c. 220–350/min d. 120–250/min e. 280–390/min',
    'context': 'Diagnoza. Pri tipični in netipični undulaciji je spodnja meja frekvence atrijev 220–250 utripov/min, zgornja pa 320–350 utripov/min. Prevajanje skozi atrioventrikularni vozel je pri tipični undulaciji v večini primerov v razmerju 2 : 1, zato je frekvenca prekatov približno 150 utripov/min. English: Diagnosis. In typical and atypical atrial flutter the lower limit of the atrial rate is 220–250 beats per minute, and the upper limit is 320–350 beats per minute. Conduction through the atrioventricular node in typical flutter is most often at a 2 : 1 ratio, so the ventricular rate is approximately 150 beats per minute.',
    'text': 'Context: Diagnoza. Pri tipični in netipični undulaciji je spodnja meja frekvence atrijev 220–250 utripov/min, zgornja pa 320–350 utripov/min. Prevajanje skozi atrioventrikularni vozel je pri tipični undulaciji v večini primerov v razmerju 2 : 1, zato je frekvenca prekatov približno 150 utripov/min. English: Diagnosis. In typical and atypical atrial flutter the lower limit of the atrial rate is 220–250 beats per minute, and the upper limit is 320–350 beats per minute. Conduction through the atrioventricular node in typical flutter is most often at a 2 : 1 ratio, so the ventricular rate is approximately 150 beats per minute. Supporting answer: 220–350/min'
  },
{
    'id': 15,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '15. The most effective method to terminate ventricular fibrillation is: a. Cardioversion b. Defibrillation c. Medications d. External cardiac massage (chest compressions) e. Artificial respiration',
    'text_answer': 'Defibrillation',
    'topic_text': '15. The most effective method to terminate ventricular fibrillation is: a. Cardioversion b. Defibrillation c. Medications d. External cardiac massage (chest compressions) e. Artificial respiration',
    'context': 'Prekatna fibrilacija Elektrokardiografsko vidimo povsem neregularne valove (slika 2.117). V hemodinamičnem pogledu pomeni zastoj srca. Potrebno je takojšnje oživljanje z masažo srca. Bolnika takoj defibriliramo (uporabimo veliko energijo in ne sinhroniziran električni sunek). English: Ventricular fibrillation On electrocardiography we see completely irregular waves (Fig. 2.117). From a hemodynamic standpoint, this means cardiac arrest. Immediate resuscitation with chest compressions is necessary. The patient must be defibrillated immediately (using high-energy, unsynchronized shocks).',
    'text': 'Context: Prekatna fibrilacija Elektrokardiografsko vidimo povsem neregularne valove (slika 2.117). V hemodinamičnem pogledu pomeni zastoj srca. Potrebno je takojšnje oživljanje z masažo srca. Bolnika takoj defibriliramo (uporabimo veliko energijo in ne sinhroniziran električni sunek). English: Ventricular fibrillation On electrocardiography we see completely irregular waves (Fig. 2.117). From a hemodynamic standpoint, this means cardiac arrest. Immediate resuscitation with chest compressions is necessary. The patient must be defibrillated immediately (using high-energy, unsynchronized shocks). Supporting answer: Defibrillation'
  },
{
    'id': 16,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '16. The AV node can generate a heart rate in the range of: a. 40–60 b. 60–100 c. 20–40 d. 40–80 e. The AV node does not have this capability',
    'text_answer': '40–60',
    'topic_text': '16. The AV node can generate a heart rate in the range of: a. 40–60 b. 60–100 c. 20–40 d. 40–80 e. The AV node does not have this capability',
    'context': 'Tako je tipična frekvenca srčnega utripa, ki jo narekuje sinusni vozel, med 60 in 80 utripov na minuto, če izvira utrip iz atrioventrikularne povezave, je frekvenca okoli 40 utripov na minuto, medtem ko je lastna frekvenca srčnega utripa prekatov okoli 30 utripov na minuto. English: Thus, the typical heart rate set by the sinoatrial node is between 60 and 80 beats per minute. If the impulse originates from the atrioventricular junction, the rate is about 40 beats per minute, whereas the intrinsic ventricular rate is around 30 beats per minute.',
    'text': 'Context: Tako je tipična frekvenca srčnega utripa, ki jo narekuje sinusni vozel, med 60 in 80 utripov na minuto, če izvira utrip iz atrioventrikularne povezave, je frekvenca okoli 40 utripov na minuto, medtem ko je lastna frekvenca srčnega utripa prekatov okoli 30 utripov na minuto. English: Thus, the typical heart rate set by the sinoatrial node is between 60 and 80 beats per minute. If the impulse originates from the atrioventricular junction, the rate is about 40 beats per minute, whereas the intrinsic ventricular rate is around 30 beats per minute. Supporting answer: 40–60'
  },
{
    'id': 17,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '17. What is the most common cause of mitral regurgitation in developed countries? a. Mitral valve prolapse b. Dilatation of the mitral annulus due to left ventricular failure c. Ischemia of the papillary muscles d. Infective endocarditis e. Rupture of a papillary muscle head',
    'text_answer': 'Mitral valve prolapse',
    'topic_text': '17. What is the most common cause of mitral regurgitation in developed countries? a. Mitral valve prolapse b. Dilatation of the mitral annulus due to left ventricular failure c. Ischemia of the papillary muscles d. Infective endocarditis e. Rupture of a papillary muscle head',
    'context': 'Najpogostejše bolezni, ki povzročijo insuficienco mitralne zaklopke, so prolaps mitralne zaklopke, revmatska vročina, infekcijski endokarditis, sistemske bolezni veziva, degenerativne spremembe v obroču (kalcinacije), ruptura hord in ishemija ali ruptura papilarnih mišic. English: The most common conditions that cause mitral valve insufficiency are mitral valve prolapse, rheumatic fever, infective endocarditis, systemic connective tissue diseases, degenerative changes of the annulus (calcifications), rupture of the chordae tendineae, and ischemia or rupture of the papillary muscles.',
    'text': 'Context: Najpogostejše bolezni, ki povzročijo insuficienco mitralne zaklopke, so prolaps mitralne zaklopke, revmatska vročina, infekcijski endokarditis, sistemske bolezni veziva, degenerativne spremembe v obroču (kalcinacije), ruptura hord in ishemija ali ruptura papilarnih mišic. English: The most common conditions that cause mitral valve insufficiency are mitral valve prolapse, rheumatic fever, infective endocarditis, systemic connective tissue diseases, degenerative changes of the annulus (calcifications), rupture of the chordae tendineae, and ischemia or rupture of the papillary muscles. Supporting answer: Mitral valve prolapse'
  },
{
    'id': 18,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '18. The most common causative agents of infective endocarditis are: a. Gram-positive cocci b. Gram-negative bacilli c. Fungi d. Cardiotropic viruses e. Intracellular bacteria',
    'text_answer': 'Gram-positive cocci',
    'topic_text': '18. The most common causative agents of infective endocarditis are: a. Gram-positive cocci b. Gram-negative bacilli c. Fungi d. Cardiotropic viruses e. Intracellular bacteria',
    'context': 'Etiologija. Mikroorganizmi, ki najpogosteje povzročajo endokarditis, so gram-pozitivni koki (viridans streptokoki, stafilokoki, enterokoki, piogeni streptokoki) in bakterije iz skupine HACEK (Haemophilus, Aggregatibacter, Cardiobacterium, Eikenella, Kingella). English: Etiology. The microorganisms most commonly causing endocarditis are gram-positive cocci (viridans streptococci, staphylococci, enterococci, pyogenic streptococci) and bacteria of the HACEK group (Haemophilus, Aggregatibacter, Cardiobacterium, Eikenella, Kingella).',
    'text': 'Context: Etiologija. Mikroorganizmi, ki najpogosteje povzročajo endokarditis, so gram-pozitivni koki (viridans streptokoki, stafilokoki, enterokoki, piogeni streptokoki) in bakterije iz skupine HACEK (Haemophilus, Aggregatibacter, Cardiobacterium, Eikenella, Kingella). English: Etiology. The microorganisms most commonly causing endocarditis are gram-positive cocci (viridans streptococci, staphylococci, enterococci, pyogenic streptococci) and bacteria of the HACEK group (Haemophilus, Aggregatibacter, Cardiobacterium, Eikenella, Kingella). Supporting answer: Gram-positive cocci'
  },
{
    'id': 19,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '19. For pain relief in myocardial infarction, we most commonly use: a. Acetylsalicylic acid (aspirin) 100 mg b. Acetylsalicylic acid (aspirin) 500 mg c. Paracetamol 500 mg d. Morphine 1 mg/kg body weight e. Morphine 0.1 mg/kg body weight',
    'text_answer': 'Morphine 0.1 mg/kg body weight',
    'topic_text': '19. For pain relief in myocardial infarction, we most commonly use: a. Acetylsalicylic acid (aspirin) 100 mg b. Acetylsalicylic acid (aspirin) 500 mg c. Paracetamol 500 mg d. Morphine 1 mg/kg body weight e. Morphine 0.1 mg/kg body weight',
    'context': 'UKREPI NA TERENU OB SUMU NA NSTE-AKS Acetilsalicilna kislina 250–500 mg per os ali vensko Nitroglicerin pršilno pod jezik pri hipertenzivnih bolnikih in bolnikih s srčnim popuščanjem Morfij za zmanjšanje bolečine do 0,1 mg/kg venski ob antimetiku Vzdrževanje SaO₂ (pulzna oksimetrija) med 94 % in 98 % z dodatkom kisika po potrebi Urgentni prevoz v regionalno bolnišnico, ki lahko v vsakem času opravi ultrazvok srca, CT prsnega koša in po potrebi ostale diagnostične preiskave English: FIELD MEASURES WHEN NSTE-ACS IS SUSPECTED Aspirin 250–500 mg, orally or intravenously Sublingual nitroglycerin spray in hypertensive patients and those with heart failure Morphine for pain relief up to 0.1 mg/kg IV (given with an antiemetic) Maintain SaO₂ (pulse oximetry) at 94 %–98 %, with supplemental oxygen as needed Urgent transport to a regional hospital capable of performing echocardiography, chest CT, and other diagnostic tests at any time',
    'text': 'Context: UKREPI NA TERENU OB SUMU NA NSTE-AKS Acetilsalicilna kislina 250–500 mg per os ali vensko Nitroglicerin pršilno pod jezik pri hipertenzivnih bolnikih in bolnikih s srčnim popuščanjem Morfij za zmanjšanje bolečine do 0,1 mg/kg venski ob antimetiku Vzdrževanje SaO₂ (pulzna oksimetrija) med 94 % in 98 % z dodatkom kisika po potrebi Urgentni prevoz v regionalno bolnišnico, ki lahko v vsakem času opravi ultrazvok srca, CT prsnega koša in po potrebi ostale diagnostične preiskave English: FIELD MEASURES WHEN NSTE-ACS IS SUSPECTED Aspirin 250–500 mg, orally or intravenously Sublingual nitroglycerin spray in hypertensive patients and those with heart failure Morphine for pain relief up to 0.1 mg/kg IV (given with an antiemetic) Maintain SaO₂ (pulse oximetry) at 94 %–98 %, with supplemental oxygen as needed Urgent transport to a regional hospital capable of performing echocardiography, chest CT, and other diagnostic tests at any time Supporting answer: Morphine 0.1 mg/kg body weight'
  },
{
    'id': 20,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '20. Primary cardiac arrest means: a. Cardiac arrest occurring in the hospital b. Cardiac arrest occurring in the field (outside the hospital) c. The cause of the arrest is intrinsic to the heart itself d. The cardiac arrest is secondary to another cause (e.g., pulmonary embolism, hemorrhage, tension pneumothorax) e. Cardiac arrest whose cause is ventricular fibrillation',
    'text_answer': 'The cause of the arrest is intrinsic to the heart itself',
    'topic_text': '20. Primary cardiac arrest means: a. Cardiac arrest occurring in the hospital b. Cardiac arrest occurring in the field (outside the hospital) c. The cause of the arrest is intrinsic to the heart itself d. The cardiac arrest is secondary to another cause (e.g., pulmonary embolism, hemorrhage, tension pneumothorax) e. Cardiac arrest whose cause is ventricular fibrillation',
    'context': 'Pri bolnikih s primarnim zastojem srca sta najpogostejši motnji srčnega ritma prekatna tahikardija brez pulza in prekatna fibrilacija. Prekatna tahikardija je redkejša in pogosto se pri prihodu ekipe nujne pomoči preide v prekatno fibrilacijo. English: In patients with primary cardiac arrest, the most common rhythm disturbances are pulseless ventricular tachycardia and ventricular fibrillation. Ventricular tachycardia is less common and often converts to ventricular fibrillation by the time the emergency medical team arrives.',
    'text': 'Context: Pri bolnikih s primarnim zastojem srca sta najpogostejši motnji srčnega ritma prekatna tahikardija brez pulza in prekatna fibrilacija. Prekatna tahikardija je redkejša in pogosto se pri prihodu ekipe nujne pomoči preide v prekatno fibrilacijo. English: In patients with primary cardiac arrest, the most common rhythm disturbances are pulseless ventricular tachycardia and ventricular fibrillation. Ventricular tachycardia is less common and often converts to ventricular fibrillation by the time the emergency medical team arrives. Supporting answer: The cause of the arrest is intrinsic to the heart itself'
  },
{
    'id': 21,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'review',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '21. Kussmaul’s sign is characteristic of: a. Superior vena cava syndrome b. Pulmonary embolism c. Constrictive pericarditis d. Left-sided heart failure',
    'text_answer': 'Constrictive pericarditis',
    'topic_text': '21. Kussmaul’s sign is characteristic of: a. Superior vena cava syndrome b. Pulmonary embolism c. Constrictive pericarditis d. Left-sided heart failure',
    'context': 'V klinični sliki konstriktivnega perikarditisa vodijo znaki desnostranskega srčnega popuščanja s hepatosplenomegalijo, ascitesom in perifernimi edemi. Zaradi pljučne kongestije se lahko pojavijo tudi dispneja, kašelj in ortopneja. Pri kliničnem pregledu ugotovimo nabrekle vratne vene. Pulzna krivulja vratnih ven je značilna in ima obliko črke W z globokim valom y, ki je posledica hitrega polnjenja prekatov v zgodnji diastoli (Friedreichov znak). Prisotna sta tudi Kussmaulov znak in paradoksni puls, ki pa je manj izrazit kot pri tamponadi. Srčna konica je slabše tipna. English: In the clinical presentation of constrictive pericarditis, signs of right-sided heart failure prevail, including hepatosplenomegaly, ascites, and peripheral edema. Due to pulmonary congestion, dyspnea, cough, and orthopnea may also occur. On examination, the neck veins are distended. The jugular venous pulse has a characteristic “W” pattern with a deep y-descent, reflecting rapid ventricular filling in early diastole (Friedreich’s sign). Kussmaul’s sign and a paradoxical pulse are also present, though less pronounced than in tamponade. The cardiac apex is poorly palpable.',
    'text': 'Context: V klinični sliki konstriktivnega perikarditisa vodijo znaki desnostranskega srčnega popuščanja s hepatosplenomegalijo, ascitesom in perifernimi edemi. Zaradi pljučne kongestije se lahko pojavijo tudi dispneja, kašelj in ortopneja. Pri kliničnem pregledu ugotovimo nabrekle vratne vene. Pulzna krivulja vratnih ven je značilna in ima obliko črke W z globokim valom y, ki je posledica hitrega polnjenja prekatov v zgodnji diastoli (Friedreichov znak). Prisotna sta tudi Kussmaulov znak in paradoksni puls, ki pa je manj izrazit kot pri tamponadi. Srčna konica je slabše tipna. English: In the clinical presentation of constrictive pericarditis, signs of right-sided heart failure prevail, including hepatosplenomegaly, ascites, and peripheral edema. Due to pulmonary congestion, dyspnea, cough, and orthopnea may also occur. On examination, the neck veins are distended. The jugular venous pulse has a characteristic “W” pattern with a deep y-descent, reflecting rapid ventricular filling in early diastole (Friedreich’s sign). Kussmaul’s sign and a paradoxical pulse are also present, though less pronounced than in tamponade. The cardiac apex is poorly palpable. Supporting answer: Constrictive pericarditis'
  },
{
    'id': 22,
