    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '22. We auscultate the aortic valve in the: a. 3rd intercostal space, right parasternal b. 3rd intercostal space, left parasternal c. 2nd intercostal space, right parasternal d. 4th intercostal space, left parasternal e. 5th intercostal space, left parasternal',
    'text_answer': '2nd intercostal space, right parasternal',
    'topic_text': '22. We auscultate the aortic valve in the: a. 3rd intercostal space, right parasternal b. 3rd intercostal space, left parasternal c. 2nd intercostal space, right parasternal d. 4th intercostal space, left parasternal e. 5th intercostal space, left parasternal',
    'context': 'Spremembe na pljučni arteriji včasih zaznamo v drugem medrebrju levo parasternalno, spremembe na aorti pa v drugem medrebrju desno parasternalno. English: Changes in the pulmonary artery are sometimes detected in the second intercostal space at the left parasternal line, whereas changes in the aorta are detected in the second intercostal space at the right parasternal line.',
    'text': 'Context: Spremembe na pljučni arteriji včasih zaznamo v drugem medrebrju levo parasternalno, spremembe na aorti pa v drugem medrebrju desno parasternalno. English: Changes in the pulmonary artery are sometimes detected in the second intercostal space at the left parasternal line, whereas changes in the aorta are detected in the second intercostal space at the right parasternal line. Supporting answer: 2nd intercostal space, right parasternal'
  },
{
    'id': 23,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Multi-vector RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '23. Peripheral arterial disease is: a. Involvement of small arteries b. Involvement of arteries distal to the knee c. A manifestation of atherosclerosis',
    'text_answer': 'A manifestation of atherosclerosis',
    'topic_text': '23. Peripheral arterial disease is: a. Involvement of small arteries b. Involvement of arteries distal to the knee c. A manifestation of atherosclerosis',
    'context': 'Opredelitev. Izraz periferna arterijska bolezen označuje kronične motnje arterijske prekrite vene. V veliki večini primerov jih povzroča ateroskleroza. Najpogosteje je prizadet spodnji ud. Bolezen se razvija počasi in je lahko dokončno asimptomatska. English: Definition. The term peripheral arterial disease refers to chronic disorders of arterial blood supply. In the vast majority of cases, it is caused by atherosclerosis. Most often the lower limb is affected. The disease progresses slowly and can remain completely asymptomatic.',
    'text': 'Context: Opredelitev. Izraz periferna arterijska bolezen označuje kronične motnje arterijske prekrite vene. V veliki večini primerov jih povzroča ateroskleroza. Najpogosteje je prizadet spodnji ud. Bolezen se razvija počasi in je lahko dokončno asimptomatska. English: Definition. The term peripheral arterial disease refers to chronic disorders of arterial blood supply. In the vast majority of cases, it is caused by atherosclerosis. Most often the lower limb is affected. The disease progresses slowly and can remain completely asymptomatic. Supporting answer: A manifestation of atherosclerosis'
  },
{
    'id': 24,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '24. Which of the following conditions is characterized by convergent (narrow‐pulse‐pressure) blood pressure? a. Severe aortic regurgitation b. Mitral regurgitation c. Cardiogenic shock d. Septic shock e. Anaphylactic shock',
    'text_answer': 'Cardiogenic shock',
    'topic_text': '24. Which of the following conditions is characterized by convergent (narrow‐pulse‐pressure) blood pressure? a. Severe aortic regurgitation b. Mitral regurgitation c. Cardiogenic shock d. Septic shock e. Anaphylactic shock',
    'context': 'Konvergentni tlak pomeni majhno razliko med sistoličnim in diastoličnim tlakom in je znak majhnega utripnega volumna in velikega žilnega upora (npr. pri kardiogenem šoku). English: Convergent blood pressure means a small difference between systolic and diastolic pressures and is a sign of a low stroke volume and high vascular resistance (e.g., in cardiogenic shock).',
    'text': 'Context: Konvergentni tlak pomeni majhno razliko med sistoličnim in diastoličnim tlakom in je znak majhnega utripnega volumna in velikega žilnega upora (npr. pri kardiogenem šoku). English: Convergent blood pressure means a small difference between systolic and diastolic pressures and is a sign of a low stroke volume and high vascular resistance (e.g., in cardiogenic shock). Supporting answer: Cardiogenic shock'
  },
{
    'id': 25,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '25. What type of heart murmurs can also be found in healthy people? a. Quiet, mid‐systolic b. Quiet, diastolic c. Quiet, that become louder with exertion d. Quiet, systolic, that radiate to the neck e. A heart murmur always means disease',
    'text_answer': 'Quiet, mid‐systolic',
    'topic_text': '25. What type of heart murmurs can also be found in healthy people? a. Quiet, mid‐systolic b. Quiet, diastolic c. Quiet, that become louder with exertion d. Quiet, systolic, that radiate to the neck e. A heart murmur always means disease',
    'context': 'Največ srčnih šumov je tihih in mezosistoličnih. Če tak šum po naključju odkrijemo pri zdravi osebi, ki ob normalni telesni aktivnosti nima težav, je potreben le natančen klinični pregled, 12-kanalni elektrokardiogram in rentgenogram prsnih organov. Če s tem ne najdemo znakov srčne bolezni, nadaljnje preiskave niso potrebne. English: Most heart murmurs are soft and midsystolic. If such a murmur is discovered incidentally in a healthy person who has no symptoms with normal physical activity, only a thorough clinical examination, a 12-lead electrocardiogram, and a chest X-ray are needed. If these do not reveal any signs of heart disease, no further investigations are necessary.',
    'text': 'Context: Največ srčnih šumov je tihih in mezosistoličnih. Če tak šum po naključju odkrijemo pri zdravi osebi, ki ob normalni telesni aktivnosti nima težav, je potreben le natančen klinični pregled, 12-kanalni elektrokardiogram in rentgenogram prsnih organov. Če s tem ne najdemo znakov srčne bolezni, nadaljnje preiskave niso potrebne. English: Most heart murmurs are soft and midsystolic. If such a murmur is discovered incidentally in a healthy person who has no symptoms with normal physical activity, only a thorough clinical examination, a 12-lead electrocardiogram, and a chest X-ray are needed. If these do not reveal any signs of heart disease, no further investigations are necessary. Supporting answer: Quiet, mid‐systolic'
  },
{
    'id': 26,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '26. What does hemoptysis mean? a. Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 mL in 24 hours b. Vomiting blood c. Coughing up bloody sputum d. Passing bloody stool e. Bloody expectoration',
    'text_answer': 'Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 mL in 24 hours',
    'topic_text': '26. What does hemoptysis mean? a. Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 mL in 24 hours b. Vomiting blood c. Coughing up bloody sputum d. Passing bloody stool e. Bloody expectoration',
    'context': 'Opredelitev. Izkašeljaj s primesjo manjše ali večje količine sveže ali že delno hematinizirane krvi imenujemo hemoptiza. Če je kri edina sestavina izmečka in jo bolnik izkašlja več kot 250 ml/24 ur, govorimo o hemoptoi. Po navadi krvavitev izvira iz bronhialne cirkulacije. ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a small or large amount of fresh or partially hemolyzed blood is called hemoptysis. If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up more than 250 ml in 24 hours, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe). The bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. English: Definition.A vacation with a substance of smaller or larger amounts of fresh or partially hematinized blood is called hemoptysis.If the blood is the only ingredient in the scum and the patient coughs it for more than 250 ml/24 hours, we are talking about hemoptoi.Usually bleeding originates from bronchial circulation.ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a Small or Large amount of Fresh or partially hemolyzed Blood is called hemoptysis.If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up the more than 250 ml and 24 house, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe).The Bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation.',
    'text': 'Context: Opredelitev. Izkašeljaj s primesjo manjše ali večje količine sveže ali že delno hematinizirane krvi imenujemo hemoptiza. Če je kri edina sestavina izmečka in jo bolnik izkašlja več kot 250 ml/24 ur, govorimo o hemoptoi. Po navadi krvavitev izvira iz bronhialne cirkulacije. ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a small or large amount of fresh or partially hemolyzed blood is called hemoptysis. If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up more than 250 ml in 24 hours, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe). The bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. English: Definition.A vacation with a substance of smaller or larger amounts of fresh or partially hematinized blood is called hemoptysis.If the blood is the only ingredient in the scum and the patient coughs it for more than 250 ml/24 hours, we are talking about hemoptoi.Usually bleeding originates from bronchial circulation.ENGLISH: Definition: Coughing up sputum mixed with a Small or Large amount of Fresh or partially hemolyzed Blood is called hemoptysis.If blood is the only component of the sputum and the patient coughs up the more than 250 ml and 24 house, we refer to it as massive hemoptysis (hemoptoe).The Bleeding usually originates from the bronchial circulation. Supporting answer: Coughing up pure blood, more than 250 mL in 24 hours'
  },
{
    'id': 27,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '27. Which investigation most easily allows us to determine the cause of acute heart failure? a. 12-lead electrocardiogram b. Chest radiograph c. Echocardiography d. Chest CT scan e. Cardiac magnetic resonance imaging',
    'text_answer': 'Echocardiography',
    'topic_text': '27. Which investigation most easily allows us to determine the cause of acute heart failure? a. 12-lead electrocardiogram b. Chest radiograph c. Echocardiography d. Chest CT scan e. Cardiac magnetic resonance imaging',
    'context': 'Transtorakalna ali transezofagealna ultrazvočna preiskava srca. Izmerimo velikost srčnih votlin, debelino prekati, ocenimo celokupno in področ­no krčenje obeh prekatov, diastolično funkcijo levega prekata, morfološke spremembe na zaklopkah in njegove funkcionalne posledice ter morebitni perikardni izliv in spremembe na velikih žilah. Zato je ultrazvočna preiskava ključna diagnostična metoda pri vseh bolnikih z akutnim srčnim popuščanjem, saj z njo pri veliki večini bolnikov ugotovimo vzrok in tudi stopnjo motenega srčnega popuščanja. Opraviti jo moramo čim prej in ob spremembah bolnikovega stanja tudi ponoviti. English: Transthoracic or transesophageal echocardiography. We measure the dimensions of the cardiac chambers, ventricular wall thickness, assess global and segmental contraction of both ventricles, diastolic function of the left ventricle, morphological changes of the valves and their functional consequences, as well as any pericardial effusion and changes in the great vessels. For this reason, echocardiography is the key diagnostic method in all patients with acute heart failure, since it allows us to determine both the cause and the severity of ventricular dysfunction in most patients. It should be performed as soon as possible and repeated if the patient’s condition changes.',
    'text': 'Context: Transtorakalna ali transezofagealna ultrazvočna preiskava srca. Izmerimo velikost srčnih votlin, debelino prekati, ocenimo celokupno in področ­no krčenje obeh prekatov, diastolično funkcijo levega prekata, morfološke spremembe na zaklopkah in njegove funkcionalne posledice ter morebitni perikardni izliv in spremembe na velikih žilah. Zato je ultrazvočna preiskava ključna diagnostična metoda pri vseh bolnikih z akutnim srčnim popuščanjem, saj z njo pri veliki večini bolnikov ugotovimo vzrok in tudi stopnjo motenega srčnega popuščanja. Opraviti jo moramo čim prej in ob spremembah bolnikovega stanja tudi ponoviti. English: Transthoracic or transesophageal echocardiography. We measure the dimensions of the cardiac chambers, ventricular wall thickness, assess global and segmental contraction of both ventricles, diastolic function of the left ventricle, morphological changes of the valves and their functional consequences, as well as any pericardial effusion and changes in the great vessels. For this reason, echocardiography is the key diagnostic method in all patients with acute heart failure, since it allows us to determine both the cause and the severity of ventricular dysfunction in most patients. It should be performed as soon as possible and repeated if the patient’s condition changes. Supporting answer: Echocardiography'
  },
{
    'id': 28,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'review',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '28. When do we say that the cardiac axis on an electrocardiogram is normal? a. If it is between 30° and 60° b. If it is between 0° and 90° c. If it is 45° d. If it is between –30° and 90° e. If it is between –60° and 120°',
    'text_answer': 'If it is between –30° and 90°',
    'topic_text': '28. When do we say that the cardiac axis on an electrocardiogram is normal? a. If it is between 30° and 60° b. If it is between 0° and 90° c. If it is 45° d. If it is between –30° and 90° e. If it is between –60° and 120°',
    'context': 'Normalna srčna os je med –30º in 90º. Med –30º in –90º je leva os, med 90º in 180º je desna srčna os. Področje med –90º in +180º imenujejo ekstremna leva ali pa nedoločena srčna os. English: The normal cardiac axis is between –30° and 90°. Between –30° and –90° it is called a left axis deviation, and between 90° and 180° a right axis deviation. The region between –90° and +180° is termed an extreme left or indeterminate axis.',
    'text': 'Context: Normalna srčna os je med –30º in 90º. Med –30º in –90º je leva os, med 90º in 180º je desna srčna os. Področje med –90º in +180º imenujejo ekstremna leva ali pa nedoločena srčna os. English: The normal cardiac axis is between –30° and 90°. Between –30° and –90° it is called a left axis deviation, and between 90° and 180° a right axis deviation. The region between –90° and +180° is termed an extreme left or indeterminate axis. Supporting answer: If it is between –30° and 90°'
  },
{
    'id': 29,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '29. How is stress echocardiography performed? a. Echocardiography using a contrast agent as stress b. An ultrasound examination after physical exercise c. An ultrasound examination before and after physical exercise d. An ultrasound examination during compression under the right costal margin e. An ultrasound examination during the Valsalva maneuver',
    'text_answer': 'An ultrasound examination before and after physical exercise',
    'topic_text': '29. How is stress echocardiography performed? a. Echocardiography using a contrast agent as stress b. An ultrasound examination after physical exercise c. An ultrasound examination before and after physical exercise d. An ultrasound examination during compression under the right costal margin e. An ultrasound examination during the Valsalva maneuver',
    'context': 'Obremenitvena ehokardiografija. Dvodimenzionalni ehokardiogram snemamo v različnih presekih pred obremenitvijo, med obremenitvijo in po njej. Obremenitev je bodisi fizična na tekočem traku ali sobnem kolesu bodisi farmakološka (npr. z dobutaminom). English: Stress echocardiography. A two‐dimensional echocardiogram is recorded in various views before stress, during stress, and after stress. The stress can be physical (on a treadmill or stationary bike) or pharmacological (e.g., with dobutamine).',
    'text': 'Context: Obremenitvena ehokardiografija. Dvodimenzionalni ehokardiogram snemamo v različnih presekih pred obremenitvijo, med obremenitvijo in po njej. Obremenitev je bodisi fizična na tekočem traku ali sobnem kolesu bodisi farmakološka (npr. z dobutaminom). English: Stress echocardiography. A two‐dimensional echocardiogram is recorded in various views before stress, during stress, and after stress. The stress can be physical (on a treadmill or stationary bike) or pharmacological (e.g., with dobutamine). Supporting answer: An ultrasound examination before and after physical exercise'
  },
{
    'id': 30,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Multi-vector RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '30. Using Doppler echocardiography and the modified Bernoulli equation, we noninvasively estimate: a. Any pressure gradient in the heart b. Only the systolic pressure in the right ventricle c. Only the gradient across a stenotic aortic valve d. Central venous pressure e. Only pulmonary arterial hypertension',
    'text_answer': 'Any pressure gradient in the heart',
    'topic_text': '30. Using Doppler echocardiography and the modified Bernoulli equation, we noninvasively estimate: a. Any pressure gradient in the heart b. Only the systolic pressure in the right ventricle c. Only the gradient across a stenotic aortic valve d. Central venous pressure e. Only pulmonary arterial hypertension',
    'context': 'Ocena tlakov. Doplerska ehokardiografija omogoča neinvazivne meritve gradientov tlakov skozi ustje zaklopk (slika 2.69). Pri toku krvi skozi ozko žilo se poveča pretočna hitrost, iz katere izmerimo razliko tlakov med sosednjima srčnima votlinama. Razmerje med razliko tlaka in hitrostjo izraža poenostavljena Bernoullijeva enačba: Δp = 4 × v² Δp je razlika v tlaku preko zožitve (mmHg), v je največja hitrost pretoka za zožitev (m/s). English: Pressure Assessment. Doppler echocardiography enables noninvasive measurement of pressure gradients across valve orifices (Fig. 2.69). As blood flows through a narrowed passage, the flow velocity increases; from this we calculate the pressure difference between the adjacent cardiac chambers. The relationship between pressure difference and velocity is expressed by the simplified Bernoulli equation: Δp = 4 × v² where Δp is the pressure difference across the stenosis (in mmHg) and v is the peak flow velocity through the narrowing (in m/s).',
    'text': 'Context: Ocena tlakov. Doplerska ehokardiografija omogoča neinvazivne meritve gradientov tlakov skozi ustje zaklopk (slika 2.69). Pri toku krvi skozi ozko žilo se poveča pretočna hitrost, iz katere izmerimo razliko tlakov med sosednjima srčnima votlinama. Razmerje med razliko tlaka in hitrostjo izraža poenostavljena Bernoullijeva enačba: Δp = 4 × v² Δp je razlika v tlaku preko zožitve (mmHg), v je največja hitrost pretoka za zožitev (m/s). English: Pressure Assessment. Doppler echocardiography enables noninvasive measurement of pressure gradients across valve orifices (Fig. 2.69). As blood flows through a narrowed passage, the flow velocity increases; from this we calculate the pressure difference between the adjacent cardiac chambers. The relationship between pressure difference and velocity is expressed by the simplified Bernoulli equation: Δp = 4 × v² where Δp is the pressure difference across the stenosis (in mmHg) and v is the peak flow velocity through the narrowing (in m/s). Supporting answer: Any pressure gradient in the heart'
  },
{
    'id': 31,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Multi-vector RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '31. What is characteristic of cardiogenic shock? a. Decreased central venous pressure b. Decreased pulmonary arterial pressure c. Decreased pulmonary capillary wedge pressure d. Decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation e. Decreased lactate concentration in arterial blood',
    'text_answer': 'Decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation',
    'topic_text': '31. What is characteristic of cardiogenic shock? a. Decreased central venous pressure b. Decreased pulmonary arterial pressure c. Decreased pulmonary capillary wedge pressure d. Decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation e. Decreased lactate concentration in arterial blood',
    'context': 'Diagnoza. Bolniki so hipotenzivni, hipoksemični, imajo presnovno acidozo s povišanim serumskim laktatom, moteno delovanje organov (motnje zavesti, oligurija). Diagnozo ob značilni klinični sliki lahko potrdimo z merjenjem hemodinamičnih spremenljivk, ki omogočajo tudi najbolj natančno specifično zdravljenje. Ugotovimo povišane polnitvene tlake ponavadi obeh prekatov, znižan minutni srčni volumen in povečano periferno ekstrakcijo kisika, ki se odraža z znižano zasičenostjo mešane venske krvi s kisikom. English: Diagnosis. Patients are hypotensive and hypoxemic, have metabolic acidosis with elevated serum lactates, and exhibit organ dysfunction (altered consciousness, oliguria). The diagnosis suggested by these clinical signs can be confirmed by measuring hemodynamic variables, which also guide the most precise, targeted treatment. Findings include elevated filling pressures upstream of both ventricles, reduced cardiac output, and increased peripheral oxygen extraction, reflected by decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation.',
    'text': 'Context: Diagnoza. Bolniki so hipotenzivni, hipoksemični, imajo presnovno acidozo s povišanim serumskim laktatom, moteno delovanje organov (motnje zavesti, oligurija). Diagnozo ob značilni klinični sliki lahko potrdimo z merjenjem hemodinamičnih spremenljivk, ki omogočajo tudi najbolj natančno specifično zdravljenje. Ugotovimo povišane polnitvene tlake ponavadi obeh prekatov, znižan minutni srčni volumen in povečano periferno ekstrakcijo kisika, ki se odraža z znižano zasičenostjo mešane venske krvi s kisikom. English: Diagnosis. Patients are hypotensive and hypoxemic, have metabolic acidosis with elevated serum lactates, and exhibit organ dysfunction (altered consciousness, oliguria). The diagnosis suggested by these clinical signs can be confirmed by measuring hemodynamic variables, which also guide the most precise, targeted treatment. Findings include elevated filling pressures upstream of both ventricles, reduced cardiac output, and increased peripheral oxygen extraction, reflected by decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation. Supporting answer: Decreased mixed venous blood oxygen saturation'
  },
{
    'id': 32,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-heart',
    'specialty': 'Cardiology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Basic RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '32. In the late period after heart transplantation, which of the following is an important factor in patient morbidity? a. Hepatitis B virus b. Influenza A (H1N1) virus c. Cytomegalovirus d. JC virus e. Adenovirus',
    'text_answer': 'Cytomegalovirus',
    'topic_text': '32. In the late period after heart transplantation, which of the following is an important factor in patient morbidity? a. Hepatitis B virus b. Influenza A (H1N1) virus c. Cytomegalovirus d. JC virus e. Adenovirus',
    'context': 'Okužba s citomegalovirusom je pomemben dejavnik, ki določa obolevnost in preživetje v poznem obdobju po presaditvi, zato je potrebno preprečevanje citomegalovirusne okužbe z uporabo valganciklovi­ra pri vseh prejemnikih, ki so visoko ali srednje ogroženi za reaktivacijo citomegalovirusa po presaditvi. English: Infection with cytomegalovirus is an important factor determining morbidity and survival in the late post–transplant period, so prevention of cytomegalovirus infection with valganciclovir is required for all recipients at high or intermediate risk for CMV reactivation after transplantation.',
    'text': 'Context: Okužba s citomegalovirusom je pomemben dejavnik, ki določa obolevnost in preživetje v poznem obdobju po presaditvi, zato je potrebno preprečevanje citomegalovirusne okužbe z uporabo valganciklovi­ra pri vseh prejemnikih, ki so visoko ali srednje ogroženi za reaktivacijo citomegalovirusa po presaditvi. English: Infection with cytomegalovirus is an important factor determining morbidity and survival in the late post–transplant period, so prevention of cytomegalovirus infection with valganciclovir is required for all recipients at high or intermediate risk for CMV reactivation after transplantation. Supporting answer: Cytomegalovirus'
  },
{
    'id': 33,
    'source_dataset': 'ChatMED-Project/RAGCare-QA',
    'tenant_id': 'hospital-general',
    'specialty': 'Endocrinology',
    'complexity': 'basic',
    'case_priority': 'high',
    'case_status': 'active',
    'rag_pipeline': 'Multi-vector RAG',
    'reference': 'Interna medicina (6. izd., str. XXXVIII, 1693). (2022). Medicinska fakulteta; Buča.',
    'question': '1. Which statement about the concentration test and desmopressin is correct? a) The patient will be treated with dDAVP b) The patient will be treated with lithium c) The patient has nephrogenic diabetes insipidus d) The patient has central diabetes insipidus e) The patient has psychogenic polydipsia',
    'text_answer': 'The patient will be treated with dDAVP',
    'topic_text': '1. Which statement about the concentration test and desmopressin is correct? a) The patient will be treated with dDAVP b) The patient will be treated with lithium c) The patient has nephrogenic diabetes insipidus d) The patient has central diabetes insipidus e) The patient has psychogenic polydipsia',
    'context': 'Central diabetes insipidus is treated with a synthetic AVP analogue, desmopressin. It acts predominantly on arginine-vasopressin V₂ receptors in the kidneys and only minimally on V₁ receptors in the vascular wall. In our practice, we use a lyophilized formulation, which the patient takes as a sublingual tablet every 12 hours; dosing every 8 hours is rarely necessary. In milder forms of the disease, a single evening dose of 1–2 tablets (60–120 µg) may suffice. Desmopressin is also available as conventional 200 µg tablets, which patients take and dose in a similar manner. The total daily requirement of desmopressin varies greatly: the range of lyophilizate doses is 60–720 µg per day, while conventional tablets range from 100 to 1000 µg per day. Desmopressin (dDAVP) is twice as potent as AVP and has a 12-hour duration of action, with minimal vasopressor effect. Dosing must be individualized for each patient by gradually titrating and monitoring fluid balance, serum osmolality, and urine osmolality. Polyuria is reduced, and nocturia is eliminated; however, one does not attempt to normalize total diuresis (to less than 2 L/day), because there is a risk of hormone overdose and consequent water intoxication (hyponatremia). The medication has almost no side effects; only very rarely do patients experience a transient sensation of head pressure, paleness, and a rapid heartbeat (vasopressor effect) shortly after dosing.',
    'text': 'Context: Central diabetes insipidus is treated with a synthetic AVP analogue, desmopressin. It acts predominantly on arginine-vasopressin V₂ receptors in the kidneys and only minimally on V₁ receptors in the vascular wall. In our practice, we use a lyophilized formulation, which the patient takes as a sublingual tablet every 12 hours; dosing every 8 hours is rarely necessary. In milder forms of the disease, a single evening dose of 1–2 tablets (60–120 µg) may suffice. Desmopressin is also available as conventional 200 µg tablets, which patients take and dose in a similar manner. The total daily requirement of desmopressin varies greatly: the range of lyophilizate doses is 60–720 µg per day, while conventional tablets range from 100 to 1000 µg per day. Desmopressin (dDAVP) is twice as potent as AVP and has a 12-hour duration of action, with minimal vasopressor effect. Dosing must be individualized for each patient by gradually titrating and monitoring fluid balance, serum osmolality, and urine osmolality. Polyuria is reduced, and nocturia is eliminated; however, one does not attempt to normalize total diuresis (to less than 2 L/day), because there is a risk of hormone overdose and consequent water intoxication (hyponatremia). The medication has almost no side effects; only very rarely do patients experience a transient sensation of head pressure, paleness, and a rapid heartbeat (vasopressor effect) shortly after dosing. Supporting answer: The patient will be treated with dDAVP'
  },
