    'question': '2. Type 1 diabetes is characterized by: a) It is predominantly immune-mediated b) It is predominantly idiopathic c) At disease onset, nearly 50% of beta cells have been destroyed d) At disease onset, about three-quarters of beta cells have been destroyed e) At disease onset, practically all beta cells have been destroyed',
