    'topic_text': '2. Type 1 diabetes is characterized by: a) It is predominantly immune-mediated b) It is predominantly idiopathic c) At disease onset, nearly 50% of beta cells have been destroyed d) At disease onset, about three-quarters of beta cells have been destroyed e) At disease onset, practically all beta cells have been destroyed',
    'context': 'Sladkorna bolezen tipa 1. Pri sladkorni bolezni tipa 1 gre večinoma za imunsko povzročeno uničenje celic beta in zato hudo pomanjkanje insulina. English: Type 1 diabetes. In type 1 diabetes mostly for the immune -induced destruction of beta cells and Therefore, severe insulin deficiency.',
    'text': 'Context: Sladkorna bolezen tipa 1. Pri sladkorni bolezni tipa 1 gre večinoma za imunsko povzročeno uničenje celic beta in zato hudo pomanjkanje insulina. English: Type 1 diabetes. In type 1 diabetes mostly for the immune -induced destruction of beta cells and Therefore, severe insulin deficiency. Supporting answer: It is predominantly immune-mediated'
