    'text': 'Context: Pod vplivom tirotropina (TSH), ki se veže na receptor za TSH (TSH-R), prehajajo delci koloida v tirocit z endoci_xFFFE_tozo, povežejo se z lizosomi v fagolizosome, sledi sprošča_xFFFE_nje T4 in T3 s tiroglobulina s pomočjo endopeptidaz (proteo_xFFFE_liza). T4 in T3 prehajata v kri skozi bazalno membrano tiro_xFFFE_cita kot prosta hormona. Večina tiroglobulina ostane v ščit_xFFFE_nici, nekaj pa ga prehaja v krvni obtok. English: Under the influence of thyrotropin (TSH) that binds to the receptor For TSH (TSH-R), the colloid particles are passed into tyrocyte with endoci_xFFFE_tosis, associated with lysosomes into phagolizomes, followed by releasing_xfffe t4 and T3 from tyroglobulin by means of endopeptidase (proteo_xfffe).T4 and T3 pass into blood through the basal membrane of the Tiro_xFFFE_cita as a free hormone.Most thyroglobulin stays in the shield_xFFFE_nica, and some passes it into the bloodstream. Supporting answer: Stimulating antibodies against the TSH receptor'
