    'question': '7. Which of the following conditions does NOT typically cause amenorrhea? a) Primary hyperparathyroidism b) Hypothyroidism and hyperthyroidism c) Addison’s disease d) Congenital adrenal hyperplasia and Cushing’s syndrome e) Virilizing tumors of the adrenal glands and ovaries',
    'text_answer': 'Primary hyperparathyroidism',
    'topic_text': '7. Which of the following conditions does NOT typically cause amenorrhea? a) Primary hyperparathyroidism b) Hypothyroidism and hyperthyroidism c) Addison’s disease d) Congenital adrenal hyperplasia and Cushing’s syndrome e) Virilizing tumors of the adrenal glands and ovaries',
    'context': 'Etiopatogeneza Funkcionalne hipotalamične amenoreje. Pogosti vzroki so dolgotrajen stres, kronične bolezni, izguba telesne teže ali premajhna telesna teža in čezmerna telesna aktivnost. Ta vrsta amenoreje se pojavlja pri anoreksiji nervozi, red_xFFFE_keje pri bulimiji. Pogosta je pri ženskah, ki intenzivno tre_xFFFE_nirajo vzdržljivostne športne zvrsti (tek na dolge proge, tek na smučeh), in pri baletkah, pri katerih se prepletata oba dejavnika – čezmerna telesna dejavnost in majhna telesna masa. Pojavlja se tudi pri rekreativnih športnicah, ki preti_xFFFE_ravajo s telesno dejavnostjo. Eden neposrednih patogenet_xFFFE_skih dejavnikov je premajhna količina telesne maščobe in zato nizka koncentracija hormona maščobnih celic – lepti_xFFFE_na, ki se na ravni hipotalamusa vpleta v urejanje hipotala_xFFFE_mo-hipofizno-gonadne osi. Organske oblike hipotalamične amenoreje so posledica okvare hipotalamusa zaradi rasti tumorja, zaradi poškod_xFFFE_be, krvavitve, okužbe (tabela 5.46). Redek vzrok hipotala_xFFFE_mične amenoreje je hipogonadotropni hipogonadizem ali Kallmannov sindrom, nastane pa zaradi motenega embrio_xFFFE_nalnega razvoja nevronov, ki izločajo GnRH, pogosto ga spremlja okvarjen voh. Bolnice imajo primarno amenorejo, puberteta ne nastopi. Incidenca bolezni je 1/10.000 novoro_xFFFE_jenih, pogosteje se pojavlja pri moških kot ženskah (4 : 1). English: Etiopathogenesis Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea.Common causes are long -lasting stress, chronic diseases, weight loss Or too little weight and excessive physical activity. This type of amenorrhea occurs in anorexia nervousness, red_xFFFE_ke in bulimia.It is common in women who intensely third_xFFFE_not endurance sports genres (long runs, running on skis), and at ballet dancers in which both are intertwined factors - excessive physical activity and small physical mass.It also occurs in recreational athletes who are threatening_xFFFE_ring through physical activity.One direct pathogenet_xfffe factors is too small a amount of body fat and Therefore, low fat cell hormone concentration-lepti_xFFFE_na, which at the hypothalamus level is involved in the regulation of the hypothal_xFFFE_mo-pomery-gonad axis. Organic forms of hypothalamic amenorrhea are the result Hypothalamus defects due to tumor growth, damage to damage_xFFFE_be, bleeding, infections (Table 5.46).A rare cause of hypothal_xFFFE_mic amenorrhea is hypogonadotropic hypogonadism or Kallmann\'s syndrome is caused by impaired embryo_xFFFE_nal development of neurons secreting GNRH, often accompanied by a defective smell.Patients have primary amenorrhea, Puberty does not perform.The incidence of the disease is 1/10,000 novoro_xFFFE_jen, more often occurs in men than women (4: 1).',
    'text': 'Context: Etiopatogeneza Funkcionalne hipotalamične amenoreje. Pogosti vzroki so dolgotrajen stres, kronične bolezni, izguba telesne teže ali premajhna telesna teža in čezmerna telesna aktivnost. Ta vrsta amenoreje se pojavlja pri anoreksiji nervozi, red_xFFFE_keje pri bulimiji. Pogosta je pri ženskah, ki intenzivno tre_xFFFE_nirajo vzdržljivostne športne zvrsti (tek na dolge proge, tek na smučeh), in pri baletkah, pri katerih se prepletata oba dejavnika – čezmerna telesna dejavnost in majhna telesna masa. Pojavlja se tudi pri rekreativnih športnicah, ki preti_xFFFE_ravajo s telesno dejavnostjo. Eden neposrednih patogenet_xFFFE_skih dejavnikov je premajhna količina telesne maščobe in zato nizka koncentracija hormona maščobnih celic – lepti_xFFFE_na, ki se na ravni hipotalamusa vpleta v urejanje hipotala_xFFFE_mo-hipofizno-gonadne osi. Organske oblike hipotalamične amenoreje so posledica okvare hipotalamusa zaradi rasti tumorja, zaradi poškod_xFFFE_be, krvavitve, okužbe (tabela 5.46). Redek vzrok hipotala_xFFFE_mične amenoreje je hipogonadotropni hipogonadizem ali Kallmannov sindrom, nastane pa zaradi motenega embrio_xFFFE_nalnega razvoja nevronov, ki izločajo GnRH, pogosto ga spremlja okvarjen voh. Bolnice imajo primarno amenorejo, puberteta ne nastopi. Incidenca bolezni je 1/10.000 novoro_xFFFE_jenih, pogosteje se pojavlja pri moških kot ženskah (4 : 1). English: Etiopathogenesis Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea.Common causes are long -lasting stress, chronic diseases, weight loss Or too little weight and excessive physical activity. This type of amenorrhea occurs in anorexia nervousness, red_xFFFE_ke in bulimia.It is common in women who intensely third_xFFFE_not endurance sports genres (long runs, running on skis), and at ballet dancers in which both are intertwined factors - excessive physical activity and small physical mass.It also occurs in recreational athletes who are threatening_xFFFE_ring through physical activity.One direct pathogenet_xfffe 